rComments: Professor Hashash barely has any information on his slides to allow you to really understand research methods. There were no labs to help us do research, and the tests had many mistakes and errors or just wouldn't have anything we spoke about in the textbook or lecture. If there is a different Prof teaching this course pick them instead!

A pretty chill guy, but his exams are DIFFICULT for me. I got a C on the midterm since there were so many detailed questions from assigned readings, guest speakers, and five-minute videos we watched in class. I spent hours every day preparing his final and finished with an A in that class.
He's awful. Dude has the whole class failing. He grades in a poor way and does not give good feedback. Sure he's a good dude but his exams are idiotic.

This guy is pretty pretentious. Tries too much to be cool in a cringe and annoying way. His exams are hard and he is a tough grader. but he seems like he cares and tries to improve so I hope he gets better!

ABSOLUTELY NOT. He is a great guy, theres no doubt about that. But his midterms, tests, and probably exams are SO DIFFICULT!!!!!!! Its okay to make us apply terms, but to be specific about guest speakers and a five minute video we watched in class?? I think not.
He does not grade based on comprehension of course content but by adherence to rubrics and information about his guest lecturers, it is inappropriate and shortsighted.

Not a fan of his grading criteria at all. He gives no feedback and isnt very helpful through emails. He gives a few questions for the quizzes which help boost your mark, but no answers nor feedback. Midterms and exams are just a pain. He isnt the worst prof ever, I just dont recommend him.

If you can avoid this class, don't take it!!! The prof is super specific and when you ask for help he reluctantly helps you. He gets frustrated easily and is rarely prepared. Exams are very difficult and he won't show you the answers or help you improve for the final.

Class content is not that when he teaches it. The midterm is way too hard for what is taught to students. Do not take this class if you can avoid it, Instructions are not clear whatsoever for the research paper. Basically, you teach this class to yourself and still won't do well.

He's a really chill prof. He is easy to approach and talk to. Always has good constructive and helpful feedback to provide. Accessible through email always. The course itself is a little heavy and intense. You really need to follow through with his teaching and take notes, ask questions. It's not that hard if you really focus on it.

rComments: Super hard and give lower grades of assignment also this prof give super hard final exam!
worst professor ever in my university life. His course is so hard, and he is so concentrated in some small details. You would lose points for just small mistakes.
this prof is not friendly and he never care about the group contribution's situation, although some students reply some situation to him
He is not friendly. NO online PPT and you cant take photos for his ppt during class time.

For his class, there is no writing on the blackboard. PPT will never post online. He just shows the PPT during class time, so you have to write down very fast. If not, then you will miss it and he will not go back again. You can not take pictures of his PPT. If you did that, he will very rude to you and let you go out!!!!
He is so mean. He can not provide help to students during his office time. He always judges problems according to his subjective impression. He is very unfair. Don't take his course !!!!!

He cannot families your face although you always ask his question after class. Also he doesn't have the peer evaluation, although your group members do not contribute to the group work, he doesn't mind and he wouldn't care about your complain. Also he do not provide study materials to you. do not take his course!!!!!!!!

He's a little pretentious and mean. He never provide ppt in the brightspace, and he not allow his students to take a picture of his ppt. Although sometimes we cannot follow him. Also he doesn't have the office hour and location, maybe you will see him in second cup. Also he will mis-recognize students and have the stereotype of you.

The course I took was 3 hours long. Pay attention and take as many notes as possible since he does not post the lectures online. Understand the videos and make sure you understand the notes for the midterm and final. There is a group project, you need to do some close research. ISPR included in this class, USE IT!
Show up and take notes, easy A. Nice guy, explains things clearly. Guest speakers are very boring. Takes attendance at random, worth a lot.

His tests are easy as heck. He gives you so many hints on what will be on the mid-term/final. I just showed up to the classes and listened to him and wrote down his slides. He doesnt post them so thats why you should show up; especially if you refuse to buy a textbook like me. We had one group project and we got an A+. He's also SUPER nice

He's a little pretentious, but his class is ridiculously easy and he gives incredibly fair midterms/ exams (he even gives out a practice test that has a decent amount of the midterm/ exam questions on it). Just attend your lectures, or find someone to send you notes, and you'll be fine

Just show up to class and read the material. So what if he doesn't post presentations on Brightspace? He's available outside of class hours by appointment if you need clarification on anything. Avoid watching crap online from your laptop during the lectures and you'll be fine.

his lecturing is really boring, plus it's research methods so it's really dry to begin with. He doesn't post slides online which sucks too, but he is a nice guy and gives you lots of cheat sheets/study notes to make exams a little easier
posts nothing on brightspace. lazy and cancels class often. Reads exactly what's on the slide and gets guest speakers who are more interesting than him to come and speak.
he doesn't post lecture online, but if you read your book then you will be fine.

The class material itself and his exam multiple choice questions are both fairly very easy. He almost always ended classes early, he also arranged a game class, which he brought candies to everybody. Overall, a very nice guy. English is not my first language, I still got 100% in the group assignment for my part.

Research methods is one of those things you have to take but no one wants as a comms student.  He was a really tough grader when I took his class last year.  The only good thing about that 7-10 research methods class was how hot he was!  Unfortunately, I did not find him very helpful. He was also a pretty dry lecturer.
Great professor who is understanding of the struggles of everyday student life!

I will never take one of his classes again. His teaching style is incredibly boring and he doesn't go in depth what so ever. His final exam review is so easy, while the test was incredibly hard. His questions were worded weirdly and the whole test is him trying to trick you. What a disappointment. Someone should report him.

He is insanely hot which was distracting sometimes.  Hard grader on assignments and some of his test questions can be confusing/weirdly worded.  He doesn't give specific enough instructions for his assignments.

Horrible professor. Teaches like it's a high school class. Final exam covered only half the material covered in class. Not very helpful, you need to show up to class to get the material, he doesn't post anything online. Irrelevant guest speakers and videos, boring lectures make this class unbearable. 8/10 would not recommend!!!

rComments: Has Pop-quizzes for participation marks - I don't think he even looks at your answers. Lectures are pretty dry and he just summarizes the textbook. Doesn't post his slides. One group assignment but it's straightforward. Exams are relatively easy but he does ask very specific questions based on the text, videos, and guest speakers.

Get ready to teach yourself subject matter. He doesn't post slides, he reads them and shows you irrelevant videos (beware there will be questions on the exam about them). Exams are tough, mc or t/f only, very wordy tries to rephrase things and trick you. Doesn't convey subject matter effectively. Gives horrible feedback on exams and group project

Doesn't post slides. His teaching style is childish - notes & videos. His exams are wordy and some of the questions will confuse you. There is a group project, but it was easy.
